e, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":20,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":45,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":58,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrix Chandos was born in 1270, in Bicton, Devon, England as the daughter of Sir Robert Chandos. She had at least 1 son with Sir William de Raleigh. She died in England."},"et":{"1270–":"1270–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1270–1365":"1270–1365","1289–1376":"1289–1376","1253–1292":"1253–1292","1315":"1315","1289":"1289","1376":"1376","1365":"1365","1253":"1253","about 1289":"umbes 1289","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Bicton, Devon, England":"Bicton, Devon, England","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, Engla